    <rigor-reason>Modifies the chat agent factory (production hot path); adds workspace snapshot to system prompt; respects 8K NFR-10 budget; gates all of 6b/6c/7/9.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G1</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire `IWorkspaceStateService` into `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` so every
    turn includes a "Workspace State" block in the system prompt summarizing currently
    open tabs that the user has marked visible to the assistant (`visibleToAssistant:
    true`). The block per spec FR-34 reads e.g. "Tab 1 (active): Summary of foo.docx
    (user-pinned); Tab 2: Document viewer for bar.pdf". Snapshot is built per-turn at
    `CreateAgentAsync` time. MUST respect the existing 8K system-prompt budget (NFR-10);
    use the shared token budget tracker (introduced later in task 068) — for now, this
    task adds the block but flags the budget interaction in task notes. Pillar 9 (task
    074) will refine by gathering each tab's `getAgentVisibleState()` output. This task
    lays the structural wiring + a minimal text summary; task 074 makes it
    schema-aware. MUST register the new dependency in existing module per ADR-010.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI-platform engineer with deep familiarity with `SprkChatAgentFactory` lifecycle
    and the `PlaybookChatContextProvider` token budget contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` queries `IWorkspaceStateService` per turn and
    appends a concise "Workspace State" section to the system prompt for tabs where
    `visibleToAssistant: true`. Respects 8K budget. Behavior with empty workspace is
    no-op (no section appended). Integration test confirms agent prompt contains expected
    workspace summary text.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="chat-architecture">docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="ai-arch">docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    <file purpose="chat-factory">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="ctx-provider">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs</file>
    <file purpose="workspace-svc">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/IWorkspaceStateService.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Inject `IWorkspaceStateService` via existing constructor pattern in factory; register in existing module. ZERO new Program.cs lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">`IWorkspaceStateService` is BFF-internal infrastructure (not AI Public Contracts); factory injection is acceptable within BFF.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Service per-tenant cache key isolation enforced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Workspace State block in prompt is data-governance-safe (tab names + widget types + provenance); MUST NOT include raw user message text from prior turns into the workspace block.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish-size delta verified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-34">Per-turn workspace snapshot included in system prompt as "Workspace State" block. Includes active tab indicator + user selection where present.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-10">8K system prompt budget preserved; truncate workspace section if it would exceed budget (log telemetry on truncation).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">Safety pipeline preserved; no middleware bypass.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project R6 Pillar 6a binding">Task 053 is the gate that ungates 6b/6c/7/9. All four downstream sub-phases depend on this wiring landing first.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff/ai-chat</topic>
