  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">"🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — Modifying chat agent factory (production hot path); gates all of 6b/6c/7/9."</step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 050-052 complete.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">Read SprkChatAgentFactory + PlaybookChatContextProvider in full; map system prompt assembly + budget tracking.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Inject Service">Add `IWorkspaceStateService` to factory constructor; register module-wise per ADR-010.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Snapshot Builder">Add private method `BuildWorkspaceStateBlock(tabs)` returning concise text; truncate if section would push past 8K budget; emit telemetry on truncation.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire into CreateAgentAsync">Insert call before final prompt assembly. No-op when no tabs visible.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Tests">Unit test factory with mock workspace service: (a) empty workspace → no block; (b) populated workspace → expected text; (c) over-budget → truncation + telemetry. Integration test confirms full agent prompt.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Publish-Size + CVE Verification">dotnet publish; vulnerable-package check.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL)">code-review + adr-check (ADR-010/013/014/015/029).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">TASK-INDEX 053 ✅; current-task → 054 (Pillar 6b/6c/7/9 NOW UNBLOCKED — main session may parallel-launch C-G2).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
